e Olympics to move into the modern era.\\\"\", \"from\": 5427, \"to\": 5483, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5436}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5453}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern era\", \"from\": 5467, \"to\": 5481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dujardin won three golds, a silver, and two bronze medals at the London, Rio, and Tokyo Games in individual and team dressage.\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5550, \"end\": 5556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999979263521, \"rank\": 2.0737747345861566e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 5558, \"end\": 5561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999996803126, \"rank\": 3.1971724200308353e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dujardin\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5493}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 5498, \"to\": 5509}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5519}, {\"ngram\": \"two bronze medals\", \"from\": 5525, \"to\": 5542}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5578}, {\"ngram\": \"individual and team dressage\", \"from\": 5582, \"to\": 5610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With six medals, she is Britain's joint-most decorated female Olympian alongside cyclist Laura Kenny.\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5637, \"end\": 5644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9974370300891061, \"rank\": 0.002568841638667483, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/